[{"indexed": {"date-parts": [[2026, 2, 11]], "date-time": "2026-02-11T14:19:26Z", "timestamp": 1770819566774, "version": "3.50.1"}, "reference-count": 0, "publisher": "IGI Global Scientific Publishing", "isbn-type": [{"value": "9798337376202", "type": "print"}, {"value": "9798337376226", "type": "electronic"}], "content-domain": {"domain": [], "crossmark-restriction": false}, "published-print": {"date-parts": [[2026, 2, 13]]}, "abstract": "<jats:p>This chapter examines AI governance in Saudi higher education through a Triple Helix model of university–government–industry integration, grounded in Saudi Vision 2030 and the National Strategy for Data and Artificial Intelligence (NSDAI). It analyzes how national strategy, regulatory requirements for data protection and cybersecurity, and institutional governance practices shape AI adoption across universities. Building on helix-based innovation theory and qualitative policy analysis, the chapter proposes a Strategic Governance Framework for Artificial Intelligence (SGF-AI) that integrates strategic alignment, ethical and legal oversight, operational coordination, and multidimensional impact evaluation. The framework is illustrated through a case study from the Applied College at King Faisal University and extended with Quadruple and Quintuple Helix perspectives to incorporate societal engagement and sustainability, concluding with a phased roadmap for 2025–2035.</jats:p>", "DOI": "10.4018/979-8-3373-7620-2.ch007", "type": "book-chapter", "created": {"date-parts": [[2026, 2, 11]], "date-time": "2026-02-11T13:41:31Z", "timestamp": 1770817291000}, "page": "187-226", "source": "Crossref", "is-referenced-by-count": 0, "title": ["Strategic AI Governance in Saudi Higher Education"], "prefix": "10.4018", "author": [{"ORCID": "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-8899-8770", "authenticated-orcid": true, "given": "Mossab Saud", "family": "Alholiby", "sequence": "first", "affiliation": [{"name": "King Faisal University, Saudi Arabia"}]}], "member": "2432", "container-title": ["Advances in Computational Intelligence and Robotics", "The Triple Helix of University-Government-Industry Partnerships and the Development of AI"], "link": [{"URL": "https://www.igi-global.com/viewtitle.aspx?TitleId=402130", "content-type": "unspecified", "content-version": "vor", "intended-application": "similarity-checking"}], "deposited": {"date-parts": [[2026, 2, 11]], "date-time": "2026-02-11T13:41:34Z", "timestamp": 1770817294000}, "score": 29.147158, "resource": {"primary": {"URL": "https://services.igi-global.com/resolvedoi/resolve.aspx?doi=10.4018/979-8-3373-7620-2.ch007"}}, "subtitle": ["A Triple Helix Model for University–Government–Industry Integration"], "issued": {"date-parts": [[2026, 2, 13]]}, "ISBN": ["9798337376202", "9798337376226"], "references-count": 0, "URL": "https://doi.org/10.4018/979-8-3373-7620-2.ch007", "ISSN": ["2327-0411", "2327-042X"], "issn-type": [{"value": "2327-0411", "type": "print"}, {"value": "2327-042X", "type": "electronic"}], "published": {"date-parts": [[2026, 2, 13]]}}, {"indexed": {"date-parts": [[2026, 4, 15]], "date-time": "2026-04-15T20:36:19Z", "timestamp": 1776285379236, "version": "3.50.1"}, "reference-count": 9, "publisher": "IGI Global", "isbn-type": [{"value": "9798369373323", "type": "print"}, {"value": "9798369373347", "type": "electronic"}], "content-domain": {"domain": [], "crossmark-restriction": false}, "published-print": {"date-parts": [[2025, 3, 13]]}, "abstract": "<jats:p>This chapter examines the strategic leadership requirements for successful AI integration in higher education institutions. Through analysis of five critical domains—enrollment management, resource allocation, financial planning, research management, and administrative operations—it explores how educational leaders can guide technological transformation while preserving institutional values. The discussion addresses AI integration approaches, organizational transformations, and leadership competencies needed for success. The analysis reveals that implementation requires careful attention to change management, stakeholder engagement, and ethical considerations. The chapter provides frameworks and recommendations for leaders navigating technological change, emphasizing the balance between innovation and tradition. Strategic guidance and future predictions help institutions prepare for AI adoption while maintaining educational excellence.</jats:p>", "DOI": "10.4018/979-8-3693-7332-3.ch020", "type": "book-chapter", "created": {"date-parts": [[2025, 3, 13]], "date-time": "2025-03-13T16:04:00Z", "timestamp": 1741881840000}, "page": "329-348", "source": "Crossref", "is-referenced-by-count": 2, "title": ["Strategic Leadership for AI Integration in Higher Education"], "prefix": "10.4018", "author": [{"ORCID": "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7417-6610", "authenticated-orcid": true, "given": "Zeina", "family": "Hojeij", "sequence": "first", "affiliation": [{"name": "Zayed University, UAE"}]}], "member": "2432", "reference": [{"key": "979-8-3693-7332-3.ch020.-1", "doi-asserted-by": "publisher", "DOI": "10.53022/oarjst.2024.11.2.0102"}, {"key": "979-8-3693-7332-3.ch020.-2", "doi-asserted-by": "publisher", "DOI": "10.1057/s41599-024-03432-4"}, {"key": "979-8-3693-7332-3.ch020.-3", "doi-asserted-by": "publisher", "DOI": "10.1007/s13384-024-00771-8"}, {"key": "979-8-3693-7332-3.ch020.-4", "doi-asserted-by": "publisher", "DOI": "10.32996/jcsts.2024.6.3.6"}, {"key": "979-8-3693-7332-3.ch020.-5", "doi-asserted-by": "publisher", "DOI": "10.1016/j.bushor.2024.05.005"}, {"key": "979-8-3693-7332-3.ch020.-6", "doi-asserted-by": "publisher", "DOI": "10.3390/su16146118"}, {"key": "979-8-3693-7332-3.ch020.-7", "doi-asserted-by": "publisher", "DOI": "10.1016/j.procs.2024.04.199"}, {"key": "979-8-3693-7332-3.ch020.-8", "doi-asserted-by": "publisher", "DOI": "10.47709/cnahpc.v6i1.3396"}, {"key": "979-8-3693-7332-3.ch020.-9", "doi-asserted-by": "publisher", "DOI": "10.55056/cte.616"}], "container-title": ["Advances in Computational Intelligence and Robotics", "Prompt Engineering and Generative AI Applications for Teaching and Learning"], "link": [{"URL": "https://www.igi-global.com/viewtitle.aspx?TitleId=372367", "content-type": "unspecified", "content-version": "vor", "intended-application": "similarity-checking"}], "deposited": {"date-parts": [[2025, 4, 11]], "date-time": "2025-04-11T17:31:04Z", "timestamp": 1744392664000}, "score": 27.91134, "resource": {"primary": {"URL": "https://services.igi-global.com/resolvedoi/resolve.aspx?doi=10.4018/979-8-3693-7332-3.ch020"}}, "subtitle": [""], "issued": {"date-parts": [[2025, 3, 13]]}, "ISBN": ["9798369373323", "9798369373347"], "references-count": 9, "URL": "https://doi.org/10.4018/979-8-3693-7332-3.ch020", "ISSN": ["2327-0411", "2327-042X"], "issn-type": [{"value": "2327-0411", "type": "print"}, {"value": "2327-042X", "type": "electronic"}], "published": {"date-parts": [[2025, 3, 13]]}}, {"indexed": {"date-parts": [[2025, 7, 30]], "date-time": "2025-07-30T13:44:07Z", "timestamp": 1753883047124, "version": "3.41.2"}, "reference-count": 104, "publisher": "SAGE Publications", "license": [{"start": {"date-parts": [[2023, 1, 2]], "date-time": "2023-01-02T00:00:00Z", "timestamp": 1672617600000}, "content-version": "tdm", "delay-in-days": 0, "URL": "https://journals.sagepub.com/page/policies/text-and-data-mining-license"}], "content-domain": {"domain": ["journals.sagepub.com"], "crossmark-restriction": true}, "short-container-title": ["FIIB Business Review"], "abstract": "<jats:p> A national education policy (NEP) is a comprehensive framework to guide education development in any country. In light of this, the present contribution is structured on an analysis of recent changes in the education policy of an emerging economy. The study is an original contribution to the qualitative study literature, applying the system model of inquiry and Twitter mining methodology using NVIVO 12 software. The sketch of the article begins by analysing the limitations and gaps of the extant education policy in an emerging country, and its implications through the SAP-LAP framework, and then analysing the reaction of various stakeholders on Twitter. The sentiment index (SI) scored +3.59, denoting a broad approval of the policy amongst the people. Further, the gap analysis develops the pathway to learning issues that guide the recommendations. The article concludes by offering a capacity development framework for better implementation and monitoring of new education policies for lower-middle income countries. </jats:p>", "DOI": "10.1177/23197145221125351", "type": "journal-article", "created": {"date-parts": [[2023, 1, 3]], "date-time": "2023-01-03T07:42:42Z", "timestamp": 1672731762000}, "update-policy": "https://doi.org/10.1177/sage-journals-update-policy", "source": "Crossref", "is-referenced-by-count": 10, "title": ["New Higher Education Policy and Strategic Plan: Commensurate India’s Higher Education in Global Perspective"], "prefix": "10.1177", "author": [{"ORCID": "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1615-8377", "authenticated-orcid": false, "given": "Khushboo", "family": "Sharma", "sequence": "first", "affiliation": [{"name": "Institute of Management Studies, Banaras Hindu University, Varanasi, Uttar Pradesh, India"}]}, {"ORCID": "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8025-1528", "authenticated-orcid": false, "given": "Vikas", "family": "Arya", "sequence": "additional", "affiliation": [{"name": "Rabat Business School, International University of Rabat, Morocco"}]}, {"given": "Himendu Prakash", "family": "Mathur", "sequence": "additional", "affiliation": [{"name": "Institute of Management Studies, Banaras Hindu University, Varanasi, Uttar Pradesh, India"}]}], "member": "179", "published-online": {"date-parts": [[2023, 1, 2]]}, "reference": [{"key": "bibr1-23197145221125351", "doi-asserted-by": "publisher", "DOI": "10.1080/13636820.2017.1303785"}, {"key": "bibr2-23197145221125351", "doi-asserted-by": "publi